708180f-a.title: Manhattan: 4th Avenue - 11th Street (East)
708180f-a.text:
Fourth Ave., at the N.E. corner of East 11th Street, showing the
new Post Office, Station ''D'' that formerly ocoupied the building at
the S.W. corner of Fourth Ave. and East 13th Street.
August 112, 1937.
George D. Chinn.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

708179f-a.title: Manhattan: 4th Avenue - 11th Street
708179f-a.text:
Fourth Ave., south from East 11th Street to Cooper Square and showing
at that point the Third Ave. Elevated Line on the Bowery. The large
5-story block front building, shown on the right is the north unit of
Wanamakers. The gothic type structures on the extreme right are the
Choir House and Hall of Grace P.E. Church.
May 7, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

711080f-a.title: Manhattan: 11th Street (East) - 4th Avenue
711080f-a.text:
(1)
East 11th Street, at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of
,Fourth Ave. Arched building shown, at the edge of demolition for the
tnew United Seates Post Office, is St. Ann's Parochial School. The ad-
joining building with a marguee is Webster Hall.
March 17, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, slightly later. Note exposed side of the church proper
(112-124 East 12th Street).
June 27, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
